SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1250
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Tom Midyett for his
service on the Tennessee Forestry Commission.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly recognize those
exemplary professionals who work with purpose and commitment to improve the quality of life of
the citizens of this State; and
WHEREAS, Tom Midyett is one such individual, who has dedicated ten years to serving
as a member of the Tennessee Forestry Commission; and
WHEREAS, appointed by Governor Bill Lee, Mr. Midyett represented the pulp and paper
industry on the State Forestry Commission for two consecutive five-year terms; and
WHEREAS, through his skillful leadership and keen guidance, Mr. Midyett has
positioned the Tennessee Division of Forestry for continued success in fire suppression,
landowner support, seedling production at the East Tennessee Nursery, and effective
management of sixteen State forests; and
WHEREAS, as Chairman of the Tennessee Forestry Commission, Tom Midyett
prioritized equipping staff with safe, modern resources; his collaborative approach secured
additional funding for the Division of Forestry, supported staff development, and ensured
adequate staffing to meet the needs of Tennessee citizens in sustaining and expanding the
State's forest resources; and
WHEREAS, he also recognized the importance of urban forests throughout Tennessee's
cities, which provide stable watersheds and public enjoyment; and
WHEREAS, Tom Midyett's vision during his tenure on the Forestry Commission has
positively influenced Tennessee's 13.8 million acres of forestland, eighty-three percent of which
are owned by private, non-industrial landowners; and
SJR1250
018531
- 1 -

WHEREAS, over the past decade, Tennessee's forest industry has contributed more
than $29 billion annually to the State's economy; Mr. Midyett's leadership has paved the way for
the Division of Forestry to expand its services and reach communities across the State; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee is most fortunate to have such a passionate champion of State
forests as Mr. Midyett, and it is fitting that we pause to recognize his contributions; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Tom Midyett for his ten
years of devoted service as a member of the Tennessee Forestry Commission, extending to
him our best wishes for much continued success in all his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
